caption: First time ordering here and the staff was friendly and helpful, the food was prepared quickly and was delicious.  Loved the grouper and cheese grits!
Loved it. Mullet and oysters Rockefeller were great.
Great staff and short waiting time! Nice atmosphere. Props to the cook, Corbin — cooked up the best burger I ever ate! 🤍
Great food best raw oysters in town. The food was fantastic.. very friendly staff..
The gumbo was certainly amazing. My dad ate 2 bowls!! The Rockefeller oysters we cooked perfectly! Staff was friendly. I will certainly be back and will go to purchase fresh seafood too!
Great food here , don’t miss out on this.
Grouper nuggets are great. An the mullet. But they were out last week
The oysters were fantastic. Yummy

The options on the menu are boring, cheese grits weren’t all that good, they actually tastes really weird. The shrimp were salty and the batter was suffocating. This place has a lot of potential if they had more refreshing, interesting options instead of just fried seafood. Overall a good place to eat if you like fried foods, but not if you’re into healthier options.

This place is great! I can't believe the low ratings by some people but then again when you read all their reviews they complain and give low ratings on all their reviews. The Food and service are Awesome! I try to eat here whenever I'm in Pensacola around lunchtime. It's a small place but 5 stars in my book. I've been here at least a dozen times and it's always good.
Great food good price
mullets jumpin 🐟

High priced but low quality seafood. Service non existent.  Went to this place for the first time today with my daughter who is in town visiting. It was disappointing. The best thing I had were the greens. They were delicious. The worst thing I had was the fried oyster appetizer. The oysters tasted old like they had turned, but luckily there was so much batter on them I could not taste the oysters anyway. I told the server the oysters were "not good." She did not even respond. The "cheese grits" were also no good. Tasted bland and like they were out of a box. No flavor. Bad texture. The grilled shrimp was pretty good, but too salty. The gumbo was a 6 out of 10. Not worth the $70 price tag for lunch. I would not go back again even if it was free. I hope this missive saves you the time and money.

Horrible experience, the lettuce was soggy & the size of a childs thumb, the fried crust was burnt severely on the side not showing, no tarter sauce was included "though clearly & specifically requested", the tomato was cut so thin it fell apart * desintigrated, the fish, (where was the GROUPER for over $10), was as thin as a piece of paper barely seen, the coleslaw was brown upon opening.  The manager blamed it on "it was a to go order" or to try them again.  The Manager also said their FOOD DETERIOATES fast when taken "to go".  WOW, that is it?  I give a minus 1 for blaming the customer for ordering "to go", never addressing the burnt crust, or the condiment issue, nor recieving requested tarter sauce, and brown cole slaw.  We asked was that it; to the manager of the restaurant @ 4:30PM 10/6/10, and he said YES.  MINUS STAR
Superb fried mullet dinner.
Love this place. Great place for a fast, delicious lunch. Also very reasonably priced seafood.

Wow, wife and I both had grouper sandwiches and they were fantastic.  Perfectly cooked and best coleslaw I have had.  Kids menu could have used a few more selections but my kids enjoyed it.  Our takeout order took 10min total.  Highly recommend.
The crab boil was so good. The store is always so clean, the staff was so nice& clean & followed the social distancing guidelines. Thank you for making my experience great.

Went there with expectations of order shrimp scampi for bride and grilled shrimp for grandson but none the having. Their web site offered shrimp scampi. I ordered grouper nuggets, not bad. So that being said i rate this place average at best.
Food and service was magnificent.

Best gumbo!  Everything they serve is delicious.  I highly recommend the debris fries and the greens.  This place is consistent - each time we go the only complaint I have is when I’m finished  because I don’t want it to be over.
I love this place!
Best fried oysters in town!

I love the Tuesday backbones, as a native and commercial fishing family we live the mullet backbones and gizzards. I only have one suggestion, cleaning the veins out of the backbones is much more appealing especially summer larger mullet and won’t take but a minute or two.
(Translated by Google) Super rich food, fresh fish  (Original) Comida super rica, pescado fresco
Omg the food was delicious.
Food was very good and the prices reasonable.  Negatives if any small and somewhat hard to find.
Very fresh Seafood, prices great!
Their fish and shrimp platter is awesome.

A smaller location with mostly counter seating. Fresh seafood is first rate. We enjoyed the shrimp po boy both grilled and fried. Each had abundant shrimp and typical sandwich dressings. The house made cocktail sauce was amazing. The restaurant was clean and odor free, the prices were reasonable. Overall a great experience.

We visited the East Hill Grill on 2/10/20 about 12:30 PM, but did not experience the 5 star rating of other customers.  Maybe it was an "off" day??  We ordered the seafood gumbo which was quite bland and watery - not as described in the menu.  The fried oysters (appetizer) were delivered to the table hot and crisp.  However, the taste was definitely lacking and had no seasoning except what was in the corn meal batter (bland).   We question that the oysters had been freshly shucked before frying as stated on the menu.  Sorry - highly unlikely we will return.
Wee Zees greens were good! Very Good Oysters! Good Food great service.
Outstanding seafood, and food
Great grouper jerk sandwich and gumbo.
Food was very tasty.  Place is clean.  Loved it
Not much in the way of "atmosphere ", but the food is amazing and the price is right.  I heartily recommend the grouper.
Came here at an odd time so our food was served very quickly. The fried fish came out hot and super fresh! All in all, a delicious meal and perfect for that seafood fix.
We stopped for lunch.  The fried flounder was fresh & delicious!  Big portions too!! 😋

Good food, nice people. Portions were really generous. Interesting service concept, you order at the counter, go sit down and they bring out your food to you. Drink station is sort of self serve. They are efficient, nice, and friendly. Good experience.
Grouper supreme sandwich and the gumbo were both great..
Really good.
The food here is absolutely amazing.   Service was prompt and courteous.
Good food
One of the better poboys I have had in the Pensacola area. I will definitely be going back for another. Also this is a very reasonably priced poboy for the area.
Good food!

Peter , The restaurant is a very beautiful tailored style also gives the feel of Old town Pensacola. Very  welcoming homey and fresh. Perfect for lunch date or casual evening. Thank you for the wonderful experience. Jodi
Good food a little high in price.

This is now our most popular spot.  The food is always cooked to perfection & the staff is always friendly.  Our relatives from Destin were here recently & that's where they wanted to eat because of how we have bragged about them.  They said they had never had fried oysters that light & delicious.
"I'll be back"...Mullet dinner was Delicious...JD said, add cornbread to the menu to go along with WeeZee's Delicious collard greens, Oh My!!! Thank You...See ya s👀n...🐟
Great food, reasonably priced. Staff needs to be more attentive. Recommended by us.
I had the mullet dinner with baked beans and french fries. Everything was seasoned well. I will most definitely be back! Oh and the sweet tea was right on point!
Was very good food was delicious very nice people
Awesome as usual. Grouper Poboy delicious. Grouper supreme sandwich with onions and green peppers to die for
Quick and good food. First of many future visits, I'm sure!
Good food but the prices are to high for this type of DIY dining.
Great food, service and staff. Will be back!
A nice cozy place specializing in excellent service and wonderful food
Small space. It's self serve everything. They bring your food out to your table after you order at the counter. Food comes out quick. Greens are great. Manager very friendly.

Today's specials were a whole flounder with hushpuppies and seafood scampi with shrimp, mussels, and scallops. I had the scampi. My aunt got the flounder with a vegetable medley.  The staff was friendly and efficient. The atmosphere was pleasant. Service was quick and the presentation was beautiful! There were TVs everywhere! I watched Alabama vs. Georgia while I ate.  It was a great dining experience. I intend to visit again very soon!
Tasty fried oysters! If you like Peg Leg Pete's, you'll love their food
Seafood was great and prepared well.

Nothing fantabulous-shrimp breading stayed on good but we're overcooked,tough. French fries were blah?? Slaw was not right. Nice waitresses,but u order urself at counter n seat urself--the smell of fish market was strong coming in n out--n pricey,w/tip $33.00??? N Mississippi mudpie was not Mississippi mudpie,more like Sara Lee fare.

caption: We had a relatively enjoyable lunch. The space is a bit small and seating is limited.  Having said that, the food, service and quality is excellent for a quick lunch.  Use the parking in the rear of the building and enter there.  The cross over odors from the adjacent fresh seafood store is not to bad.  Most importantly to me the iced tea is fresh.
This place is great. The best Hush Puppies around. Great food, everyone was very nice and it was quick service.
Prior  experiences there were awesome!!! Today, french fries for husband and I were warm and soft. His fish was nice and hot, mine, so.
Always have to come here to get my shrimp when I come back home to Pensacola
Very good. You can sure tell it's fresh.
Mullet Dinner.  Never had mullet before...not loving the tail and backbone, but it was good.  Loved the fries, not a huge fan of the cole slaw.

Food was Great, Friendly Staff, Very Clean.  Had the fried Fresh Catch and the Grouper Supreme, one with fries the other with sweet potato tots.  I would prefer the sweet potato tots before the fries.  The fries to me tasted like ore ida crinkle cut but the tots were fantastic.  Fish portions on sandwich was plenty for dinner.   Although the Fried Fresh Catch that you get at Sidelines is a much bigger portion of fish. It always hangs way off the bun.  I always take half my sandwich home at Sidelines.  Would go there again, overheard that the grits and the mullet were delicious.

Disappointed in our experience today, as we really enjoy Peglegs and Sidelines. The mullet were not served in whole filets, but small pieces instead. My husbands fried oysters app were sitting in grease when served. The hush puppies were tasty but somewhat under cooked. Perhaps they will improve in the future, but I think we will stick to Jerry’s for mullet and grouper dinners.
The food is fresh and cookef to perfection. I love it when you walk in and the young black guy welcome you. Just so you all know wevwe been there more times than I can count.
Excellent food and staff!

I really wanted to like this place. However, they got my order wrong and it took quite some time to correct it. The fried mullet was extremely spicy - which should have been noted on the menu. It wasn’t a very pleasant surprise, and I wouldn’t have ordered it if I had known.

The chicken tenders were delicious, perfect breading to chicken ratio. We got the mild sauce and it was exactly what we needed. We also really enjoyed the roast beef debris sandwich- get it with cheese! 10/10 will be back.
Don is a great front man, made our first of many visits excellent. Everything we ordered was as good as any I’ve had and better than most
Fried shrimp was fresh, crisp, and hot. The mullet is caught that day. Hush puppies had just to write amount of onion and spices and are made from scratch.
Great food And 6 blocks from the house
Friendly staff, clean restaurant & excellent food! Highly recommend

I am going to go ahead and give this place five stars and attribute the thought of giving it four to growing pains from its recent opening. We went in for dinner on June 2nd, and the young man on the register was very kind and helpful. The smoked tuna dip was excellent, as were the greens. The grouper fillet on my sandwich was cut so that there was a fishy portion, but the rest of the cut was good. We will be back and will try more menu items.
